      "content": "hey im working on this embedded c++ project and the heap just keeps growing till it crashes. i think there is a leak somewhere in this class. can u take a look?\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n\nclass SensorData {\npublic:\n    SensorData(int val) : value(val) {\n        buffer = new int[100];\n    }\n    ~SensorData() {\n        // i thought i was handling it here\n    }\n    void process() {\n        std::cout << \"Processing: \" << value << std::endl;\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    int value;\n    int* buffer;\n};\n\nvoid run_sensor_loop() {\n    for (int i = 0; i < 1000; ++i) {\n        SensorData* data = new SensorData(i);\n        data->process();\n        // i keep forgetting to clean up something\n    }\n}\n\nint main() {\n    run_sensor_loop();\n    return 0;\n}\n```\nis it the new in the loop or the buffer?",
